Barofsky Says BofA Would Be Bailed Out if Needed

-- B y  
-- 
2011-09-22T13:37:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/barofsky-says-bofa-would-be-bailed-out-if-needed-video.html
Neil Barofsky, former special 
inspector general for the U.S. Treasury's Troubled Asset Relief 
Program and a Bloomberg Television contributing editor, talks 
about Moody's Investor Service's downgrade of Bank of America 
Corp.'s credit rating and the outlook for the Dodd-Frank 
financial regulatory overhaul.  Barofsky speaks with Erik Schatzker and Deirdre Bolton on 
Bloomberg Television's "InsideTrack." (Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 03:25
 